 VIRTUAL_SITES_COM, i.e., center of mass. * Add a new implementation
 VIRTUAL_SITES_RELATIVE for rigid-body like objects

2011-01-26 Dominic <dominic@icp.uni-stuttgart.de>

 * lb_boundaries_gpu.c, lbgpu.cu, lbgpu_cfile.c: lbgpu code clean up for
 release

2011-01-26 kosovan <kosovan@icp.uni-stuttgart.de>

 * doc/ug/inter.tex: Update to Debye-Hueckel documentation

2011-01-26 Stefan Kesselheim <kessel@tahr.ica1.uni-stuttgart.de>

 * statistics.c: analyze momentum can now be called also without LB

 * constraint.c, constraint.h, interaction_data.h: conical pores and
 reflecting walls added  Both are extensions to the constraint concept: Pores
 can have two different radii, given by its args radii ( replacing the arg
 radius ) that corresponds to both pore openings. Additionally the constraint
 sphere cylinder and pore can have the property of being reflecting, i.e.
 penetrating particles are reflected a) in a elastic fashion or b) in a
 "bounce back" fashion.

2011-01-25 Stefan Kesselheim <kessel@tahr.ica1.uni-stuttgart.de>

 * lb.c: Some changes to lb.c were not included in last comit  now I added
 them

